<HEADLINE> China Provides Solar Energy Technology to Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, February 27 (Xinhua) -- China is using advanced solar
energy technology to help meet the energy demand in Harare,
capital of Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
According to a local source, solar energy equipment will soon
be flown to Harare from Hangzhou, capital of east China's Zhejiang
Province,
</P>
<P>
The equipment will be provided and operated by Zhejiang
Provincial Energy Research Institute and Zhejiang Meida Solar
Energy Industry Corporation Ltd.
</P>
<P>
China provided solar systems to rural households in Zimbabwe to
generate electricity in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Many other African countries have shown great interest in
purchasing solar energy technology from Zhejiang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
